{"detail":"Here are the concrete facts for the planner:\n\n---\n\n## Project Context\n\n| Fact | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Language** | TypeScript (strict) |\n| **Framework** | SvelteKit (Svelte 4) |\n| **Test runner** | Vitest (`vitest run`), with jsdom environment |\n| **Relevant module path** | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/` |\n| **Module entry point** | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/index.ts` |\n| **Build** | `tsc --noEmit` for type-checking; `vite build` for production |\n\n## Text-utilities module structure\n\nThe directory `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/` contains five files:\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `normalize-text.ts` | Internal pure function: collapses all whitespace runs to single spaces, trims. Used by every other function. |\n| `word-count.ts` | Public `wordCount(text)` — normalizes then splits on `' '`, returns length (or 0 for empty). |\n| `truncate-words.ts` | **Public `truncateWords(text, maxWords)`** — the subject of this issue. |\n| `index.ts` | Barrel re-exports `normalizeText`, `wordCount`, `truncateWords`. |\n| `index.test.ts` | Vitest suite covering all three exported functions (11 `normalizeText` cases, 9 `wordCount` cases, 16 `truncateWords` cases). |\n\n(Note: `estimateReadingTime` mentioned in the issue body does **not** appear in the current codebase — that appears to be a separate concern from a prior issue #54.)\n\n## `truncateWords` implementation (`truncate-words.ts`)\n\nThe function is already **fully implemented** with the exact signature and behavior the issue requests:\n\n```\nexport function truncateWords(text: string, maxWords: number): string\n```\n\n**Logic flow:**\n1. `if (maxWords <= 0) return '';`\n2. Normalize via `normalizeText(text)` — reusing the same tokenizer as `wordCount`.\n3. `if (normalised === '') return '';`\n4. Split on `' '` → `words`.\n5. If `words.length <= maxWords` → return `normalised` unchanged (no ellipsis).\n6. Otherwise → `words.slice(0, maxWords).join(' ') + '…'` (U+2026).\n\n## Acceptance criteria coverage (all met)\n\n| Criterion | Covered by |\n|-----------|------------|\n| Exported from text-utilities module | `index.ts:3` — `export { truncateWords } from '.\/truncate-words';` |\n| `<= maxWords` → unchanged, no ellipsis | Line 52: `if (words.length <= maxWords) return normalised;` |\n| `> maxWords` → first N + `\"…\"` | Line 53: `words.slice(0, maxWords).join(' ') + '…';` |\n| `maxWords <= 0` → `\"\"` | Line 49: `if (maxWords <= 0) return '';` |\n| Whitespace-only\/empty → `\"\"` | Lines 50–51: normalize then check empty |\n| Reuses existing tokenization | Uses `normalizeText` (same as `wordCount`) — no independent splitter |\n\n## Test coverage (`index.test.ts`, `truncateWords` block)\n\n16 test cases covering:\n- `maxWords = 0`, `maxWords = -1`, `maxWords = -Infinity` → `\"\"`\n- Empty string, whitespace-only with positive maxWords → `\"\"`\n- Fewer words than max → normalized text returned as-is\n- Exactly maxWords → normalized text returned as-is\n- Leading\/trailing whitespace handled in both under-limit and at-limit cases\n- More words than max → truncated + `…`\n- Single word edge cases (maxWords=1 with 1 word vs multi-word)\n- Extra whitespace between words before truncation\n\n## Call sites\n\nNo external consumers of `truncateWords` yet — `find_references` returned no results outside the text-utilities module itself. This is a greenfield addition with no migration burden.\n\n---\n\n## Verdict\n\n**The work item is already done.** The `truncateWords` function exists, is exported, is tested with all acceptance-criteria edge cases, and reuses the module's existing `normalizeText` tokenization. No code changes are required. The implementation and tests match the issue specification exactly.","ticketId":"58","phase":"planning","outcome":{"note":{}},"at":804617862.53613,"id":"58-140"}
